2013-12-23|2013-12-29.description:
A FOREVER EVIL tie-in! Why has the Crime Syndicate really come to our Earth? What are their darkest secrets? And how will their actions fundamentally change the Justice League as we know it? Meanwhile, Grid controls the world’s power and communications, but what does he truly want from the Syndicate? Plus, a member of the League struggling to survive plots a path of return...and revenge.

2013-12-30|2014-01-05.description: A sweeping visual tale of Gotham City’s forgotten citizens: the abused and the voiceless. Will these desperate souls find their angel in The Dark Knight? Find out in this special mostly silent issue.
2013-12-30|2014-01-05.name: Voiceless, Part One of Two

2013-12-30|2014-01-05.description: Kate Kane's life has always been one of intrigue and adventure, but since she took on the mantle of Batwoman, things have been in overdrive with no sign of slowing down! Join us as Batwoman starts her next chapter and faces a threat that might just have her rethinking her career as a hero!
2013-12-30|2014-01-05.name: Webs, Part One: Strands

2013-12-30|2014-01-05.description: “Sea of Storms” begins with the debut of new AQUAMAN writer Jeff Parker! The Earth’s crust is grinding to life, releasing deadly volcanoes and bizarre creatures…so humanity’s first instinct is to blame Atlantis! And as the plates pull apart, the pressures of ruling a kingdom under siege are weighing on Aquaman and Mera as well!
2013-12-30|2014-01-05.name: Pressure

2013-12-30|2014-01-05.description: A FOREVER EVIL tie-in! The Crime Syndicate’s Sea King, last seen at the end of “Trinity War,” has cheated death and plagues the JL Dark team!
2013-12-30|2014-01-05.name: Forever Evil: Blight - The Haunted Sea

2013-12-30|2014-01-05.description: A RED WILL BE DEAD! It’s Guy Gardner and five Red Lanterns on their first mission in Sector 2814—a planetary army a billion strong, led by the evil fascist dictator Field Marshal Gensui. How can they all possibly survive? In fact, not all of them do!
2013-12-30|2014-01-05.name: Red. Dead.

2013-12-30|2014-01-05.description: Trapped in modern times, Jonah Hex sets out to find the money he left buried around the southwest. But a chance encounter with John Constantine sets the Civil War vet on a collision course with the occult.
2013-12-30|2014-01-05.name: What is and What Will Never Be

2013-12-30|2014-01-05.description: Catwoman’s adventure in the Gotham Underground comes to a deadly end as she tries to pull off a heist by pitting Doctor Phosphorus, Warhog and The Joker’s Daughter against each other!
2013-12-30|2014-01-05.name: Diamonds are a Girl's Worst Friend

2013-12-30|2014-01-05.description: In this special standalone story, The Flash loses someone important to him. To catch the villain responsible, The Flash must figure out how to use his powers in the one place where they do him little good: the sky!
2013-12-30|2014-01-05.name: Flash Out of Water

2013-12-30|2014-01-05.description: In the aftermath of “Krypton Returns,” a distraught Man of Steel returns to find that the Parasite is back—and he is very hungry. First on the menu: Lois Lane!
2013-12-30|2014-01-05.name: Brain Drain

2013-12-30|2014-01-05.description: Secrets are revealed and trusts tested as the Teen Titans finally begin to understand Kid Flash’s criminal actions before he became a heroic member of the team.
2013-12-30|2014-01-05.name: You Can't Go Home Again

2013-12-30|2014-01-05.description:
The rebellion on Sakaar goes on! As the deciding battle moves closer, have the Hulk and his fellows to join forces against the forces of the Red King. But even if they succeed, to overthrow his cruel regime, it remains to be seen, if the Hulk really can bring peace to this torn world.

Collects: The Incredible Hulk (Vol. 2) #100-105 & Amazing Fantasy #15
2013-12-30|2014-01-05.name: Vol. 46 - Der unglaubliche Hulk - Planet Hulk, Teil 2

2013-01-14|2013-01-20.description: A series of robberies continue to hit Riverdale and Jughead is worried the Chok'lit Shoppe could be next. Will the robber be caught before it's too late? Reggie's head is still spinning from the suddenness of his father's heart attack and to top it off he's been saddled with the responsibility of overseeing the family business. Can he make his father proud? But not everyone is filled with worry as Cheryl recovers from cancer and may have just met a potential mate. Is love in the air?
2013-01-14|2013-01-20.name: Over Our Heads Part Two: Ups and Downs

2013-01-14|2013-01-20.description: Archie settles in as president of Mirth Records but is soon disillusioned when he discovers that the "talent" may not be so talented after all. Recovering from his gunshot wound, Clay discovers what it's like to be on the other side of physical therapy. Meanwhile, Reggie is given a choice by his reality show producer: up the drama with fake fighting between him and Betty or face cancellation. How will Betty take this?
2013-01-14|2013-01-20.name: Politics As Usual Part Two: All In A Days Work!

2013-01-14|2013-01-20.description: "Archie Marries Veronica" - Archie settles in as president of Mirth Records but is soon disillusioned when he discovers that the "talent" may not be so talented after all. Recovering from his gunshot wound, Clay discovers what it's like to be on the other side of physical therapy. Meanwhile, Reggie is given a choice by his reality show producer: up the drama with fake fighting between him and Betty or face cancellation. How will Betty take this? Reggie's head is still spinning from the suddenness of his father's heart attack and to top it off he's been saddled with the responsibility of overseeing the family business. Can he make his father proud? But not everyone is filled with worry as Cheryl recovers from cancer and may have just met a potential mate. Is love in the air?
2013-01-14|2013-01-20.name: All In A Day's Work; Over Our Heads

2013-02-04|2013-02-10.description: The shape-shifting 100-point alien boss has finally been destroyed—along with much of Osaka—and Kei Kurono is back on the team, resurrected after his second death. But good times never last as the Gantz orb reveals a countdown clock showing that Earth has just over a week before catastrophe strikes, and the Tokyo team is whisked to Italy to face a new set of deadly foes on what what may be their final mission!
2013-02-04|2013-02-10.name: Volume 26

2013-02-04|2013-02-10.description: The third year of Dynamite's Vampirella starts here! There's a new dawn on Earth, and a new beginning for Vampirella in the aftermath of war. Who are Mother Rowan and the Sleepless Boys, and why have they called for our heroine's help? A Dynamite Done-In-One, perfect for longtime fans and new readers!
2013-02-04|2013-02-10.name: The Sleepless Boys

2013-02-04|2013-02-10.description: With a slight lead thanks to Mitsui, Shohoku has their hands full as the game against Sanno heats up. Sanno's coach Domoto sends in Mikio, a player whose strength and size make up for his lack of experience. Coach Anzai counters by telling Shohoku to run their offense through Sakuragi, and the game becomes a battle between the two inexperienced power players. What Sanno thought would be an easy win for them is turning out to be a lot more than they bargained for - Shohoku's here and they mean to go all the way to the top!
2013-02-04|2013-02-10.name: Vol. 26

2013-02-18|2013-02-24.description: Archie, Betty and Veronica's parents are all going out for dinner, leaving their respective teens behind to fret over what subjects will arise during dinner conversation. Will their secrets be spilled? Will they be embarrassed beyond words? Worse yet, will the famous love triangle tear their families apart? "Dinner for 6" holds all the answers and you're invited to take part!

2013-02-25|2013-03-03.description: Transformed by the forces of The Void into the embodiment of Death itself, Hope is about to be put to the test in a most horrifying manner. Lying in ruins and abandoned for nearly a decade, Castle Death beckons, but Lady Death finds that it is anything but deserted, as deadly apparitions of those she has slain haunt it and cry out for vengeance.

2013-03-11|2013-03-17.description:
Jason Aaron and Eisner-Award winning best artist Ramón Pérez continue the arc that readers will remember for years to come.

Dog Logan is back and Wolverine is in for a world of hurt. Plus, danger in the Savage Land!
2013-03-11|2013-03-17.name: Savage Learning Part 2; A Boy Named Dog

2013-03-18|2013-03-24.description: Tom Judge's plans to recruit Witchblade bearer Sara Pezzini in his quest to overthrow Darkness bearer Jackie Estacado didn't pan out quite the way he expected. In a desperate grasp to turn his fortunes in battle, Tom has turned his attention to attacking the perversion of the universe Jackie created at its core. But will Tom do what needs to be done when he must brace himself to end the life of an innocent bystander?
2013-03-18|2013-03-24.name: Progeny, Part 4

2013-03-25|2013-03-31.description: Garth Ennis' return to Crossed continues with the second brutal issue of "The Fatal Englishman." What drives men in an insane world? Facing pure and utter hatred, these soldiers are learning the hard lesson that there is no hope...
2013-03-25|2013-03-31.name: The Fatal Englishman, Part Two

2013-04-01|2013-04-07.description: Archie's friend Cricket O'Dell has a unique ability to smell money down to the penny! When an allergic reaction causes Cricket's sniffer to foresee how much money a person will possess in the near future, she makes the startling prediction that Mr. Lodge will soon be penniless and Archie's about to be loaded! But how could that be? Is Cricket's fore-smell way off? Check out "Fortune Telling" and see what the future holds!
2013-04-01|2013-04-07.name: Fortune Telling

2013-04-01|2013-04-07.description: So what happened between Tommy and Laurel during the five years that Oliver was presumed dead? Find out in this steamy chapter!
2013-04-01|2013-04-07.name: Lapse

2013-04-08|2013-04-14.description: Translates Avengers #30, Avengers Academy #33 and New Avengers #30.

2013-04-22|2013-04-28.description: Season 2 of the smash hit series begins here, with a special, full-sized, impossibly priced $1 prelude - the perfect jumping-on point for collection readers looking to move to single issues!
2013-04-22|2013-04-28.name: The Waiting Game

2013-04-22|2013-04-28.description: Stone-cold vigilante Jennifer Blood is no longer trapped in the confines of the domestic life. No, now she's the most notorious inmate of Las Chacales Women's Correctional Facility... and she fears that she's been targeted by someone beyond the bars and barbed wire. Who could possibly have the connections and inclination to reach her in prison?
2013-04-22|2013-04-28.name: Opening Up

2013-04-29|2013-05-05.description:
"NATURAL RESOURCES" CONTINUES!

Fortress Utopia!

The Mutant Nation is Under Siege! And General Ross is leading the charge!!

Can Kitty and Mach Two work together for the good of mutantkind?!

Jimmy Hudson prepares for war!!
2013-04-29|2013-05-05.name: Natural Resources, Part Three

2013-05-20|2013-05-26.description:
A DOUBLE-SIZED EXTRA-vaganza celebrating the third-year of the acclaimed series!

Face to face with his opposite number--a foe Daredevil cannot beat!

What is his connection to the accident that created Daredevil?

PLUS: As Foggy deals with his cancer, Matt turns to one of the brightest guys in the galaxy for help.

Here comes...Iron Man!
2013-05-20|2013-05-26.name: Punching Cancer

2013-05-20|2013-05-26.description: Translates X-Men: The Hidden Years #0-22, X-Men #94 & The Incredible Hulk Annual 7.
2013-05-20|2013-05-26.name: Partrull-X: Los años perdidos

2013-06-10|2013-06-16.description: The historic Sonic the Hedgehog and Mega Man crossover event rolls on! The hunt for the Roboticized Masters continues as Sonic and Mega Man face down Shadow Man and - Shadow Man? Meanwhile, Drs. Eggman and Wily gloat over the captive Dr. Light. But what is the brilliant, bearded scientist preparing to do? Featuring stunning new cover art from Patrick 'SPAZ' Spaziante, and a special throwback variant cover you just can't miss!
2013-06-10|2013-06-16.name: When Worlds Collide Part 7: Evening the Odds

2013-06-10|2013-06-16.description:
MASTER AGAINST MASTER

Just as the S-class wizard test gets underway, everything goes wrong! Grimoire Heart launches a surprise attack on Fairy Tail. But the guild is just collateral damage – their real goal is much more sinister. At the vanguard of the invasion force is Grimoire Heart’s master, Hades… a man who only respects power, and has a history with Makarov!

ULTIMATES DISASSEMBLED PART TWO!!!

A new dark force has taken the reigns of the world

The Ultimates are no more. Long live the XXREDACTEDXX

After these recent events, the royal family insists that she take a quiet, safe holiday. But her sojourn of relaxation turns into a nightmare, as the young princess bears witness to a dangerous discovery in an unknown region of Barsoom!

2013-06-24|2013-06-30.description:
Astro Boy has been badly banged up and there's no one else to stop Deadcross's dastardly plans! Can Mustachio rescue Astro Boy? Even if he can, how will anyone be able to fix him in time to stop Deadcross from forcing President Rag to resign?! Also included are Buddha, Dororo, and Black Jack.

2013-07-01|2013-07-07.name: Undercloud, Part Six: Extended Family

2013-07-08|2013-07-14.description: In the Fortress of Solitude, the Kents confront Luthor over his plans to give other people super powers. Meanwhile, Superman confronts the Flash over...a game of chess?
2013-07-08|2013-07-14.name: Chapter 26

2013-07-15|2013-07-21.description: John Carter might be the brand-new Warlord of Mars, but his his honeymoon's gonna be real short. The savage green Martians start running amok the moment he ascends the throne, threatening to smash the fragile peace he has fought so hard to win. What's behind the uptick in violence? Only John Carter and his old pal Tars Tarkas can find the truth. Warlord of Mars #26 is the first installment of the thrilling Savages of Mars story arc. John Carter's exploits on the Red Planet are just beginning!
2013-07-15|2013-07-21.name: The Green Menace: Savages of Mars Part 1 of 6

Meet the Juice Squeezers: a group of elementary-school kids tasked with secretly keeping their small town safe from a horrible, underground epidemic—written and drawn by David Lapham! Join bounty hunter Mercy St. Clair on a vacation gone horribly wrong in Ron Randall’s Trekker!

David Lapham writes and draws a gory all-ages story.

2013-08-12|2013-08-18.description: Is the Il Palazzo commanding ACROSS real or fake, and what does that mean, exactly? The original reunited team of Excel, Hyatt and Elgala stand before the throne of their lord—only for Excel to perform a blasphemous gesture of disloyalty, and for Il Palazzo to issue the most shocking order Excel could ever imagine! As Shiouji comes to realize the truth about both his father and his mother, Matsuya is ready to make a decision that will open the forbidden door at last. Warning: you have been misled!
2013-08-12|2013-08-18.name: Vol. 26

2013-08-26|2013-09-01.description:
"SPIDER-MAN NO MORE" CONTINUES

SPIDER-MAN is back!!

Will CLOAK, DAGGER, BOMBSHELL, SPIDER-WOMAN and SPIDEY be enough to take down the evil ROXXON CORPORATION?

And what is Miles' new girlfriend's secret?
2013-08-26|2013-09-01.name: Spider-Man No More, Part 4; Ultimate Amazing Fantasy #14 - Here Comes... Bombshell

While Leonardo and the Foot bring the fight to the Savate ninjas, the other Turtles call upon all of their allies to prepare for War. City Fall continues to escalate when Splinter crosses a line by helping Old Hob get his revenge!

2013-10-21|2013-10-27.name: Flowers for Bizarro, Part 2 of 3

2013-10-21|2013-10-27.description: The conflict between the Klingon and Romulan Empires erupts, with Captain Kirk and the crew of the Enterprise trapped in the middle! Don't miss the newest chapter of the ongoing series overseen by Star Trek Into Darkness writer/producer Roberto Orci!
2013-10-21|2013-10-27.name: The Khitomer Conflict, Part 2 of 4

2013-11-11|2013-11-17.description: This issue is filled with sick humor! Because SpongeBob has a bad cold. And when his friends visit, things somehow get worse. Joey Weiser and Gregg Schigiel reveal all in 'Sick Day.' And in 'Trench Vanilla,' readers can experience a SpongeBob adventure in widescreen - that's right, it's a 10-page comic that is one continuous image! Enjoy this miracle of comic book technology courtesy of Robert Leighton and Gregg Schigiel. Plus: James Kochalka's 'SpongeFunnies,' David Lewman and Vanessa Davis' 'Squidward in Love,' Joey Weiser's 'Phoney Dance Party,' and Maris Wicks' 'Flotsam and Jetsam.'

2013-11-18|2013-11-24.description: From Barsoom to the cold winds of Cimmeria, Draw!, the professional 'how-to' magazine on comics and animation, interviews legendary illustrator Joe Jusko as he explains and illustrates his process creating some of the top fantasy art being produced today! Plus, Jamar Nicholas interviews Jimm Rugg, the artist behind Street Angel and The Guild. Draw! also welcomes new regular contributor Jerry Ordway with the debut of a regular feature on his behind-the-scenes working process as an industry legend.

2013-12-02|2013-12-08.description: Batman works to contain a swarm of genetically altered killer bats, as well as She-Bat and other humans who have been mutated into bat-people.
2013-12-02|2013-12-08.name: Crown of Fear

2013-12-02|2013-12-08.description: Luke’s journey to Italy gets him deeper into the criminal underworld – unfortunately for him, that means fighting superpowered villains in a death tournament where he can’t use the Batwing armor!
2013-12-02|2013-12-08.name: When in Rome (Sort of)

2013-12-02|2013-12-08.description: All hell breaks loose as Superman is caught between an alien menace and the super-powered soldier the U.S. Army has sent to kill it!
2013-12-02|2013-12-08.name: Monster

2013-12-02|2013-12-08.description: “THE OUTSIDERS WAR” begins here! Oliver Queen finally knows the location of the Outsiders’ base, but first he must return to the place where Green Arrow was born: The Island! Secrets are revealed, new villains introduced, and a mind-blowing final page kicks off this new storyline with a bang!
2013-12-02|2013-12-08.name: The Outsiders War, Book 1: Return to the Island

2013-12-02|2013-12-08.description: Still in disarray after the events of “LIGHTS OUT,” Hal and Kilowog struggle to enforce the Corps’ new directive against Star Sapphire Nol-Anj! Having revealed a command of the Violet light unlike any the Corps has encountered before, Hal makes an earth-shaking decision. Is his win-at-all-costs attitude exactly the kind of leadership the Corps needs, or is he walking them into their next trap?
2013-12-02|2013-12-08.name: Superior Force

2013-12-02|2013-12-08.description: The Avatar of the Green has something to prove, and he’s going to do it by killing Animal Man and/or destroying the world—not necessarily in that order! Plus, the origin of Swamp Thing’s newest foe, the implacable Seeder, in a story filled with cameos from some of the DCU’s darkest magical denizens!
2013-12-02|2013-12-08.name: Victor: Spoiled

2013-12-02|2013-12-08.description: Storm Control decides to trade one peril to Earth for another while Stormwatch teams up with a mega-powered cosmic dynamo, and we finally get to meet Extremax the Omega in the flesh!
2013-12-02|2013-12-08.name: Legacy

2013-12-02|2013-12-08.description: He's fought everything from giant robots to bionic bigfoot and lived to tell about it. But when Steve's best friend becomes his mortal enemy it will be the fight of his life. When the smoke clears, the Bionic Man and OSI will be changed forever.

Daredevil battles Psylocke! The Avengers challenge the power of the X-Men! The long-lost secrets of the Iron Fist are revealed!

By Brian Michael Bendis, Mike Dedoato, Rick Remender and Brandon Peterson!

Includes material reprinted from: Avengers vs X-Men #6, AVX #6, New Avengers #26 and 29.

2013-12-09|2013-12-15.description: ZERO YEAR continues! With Gotham City thrown into total chaos by The Riddler, Batman and Jim Gordon must learn to work together! This issue is also offered as a combo pack edition with a redemption code for a digital download of this issue.
2013-12-09|2013-12-15.name: Zero Year: Dark City, Part Three

2013-12-09|2013-12-15.description: With the events of FOREVER EVIL looming, Nightwing enters the final stages of life as he knows it!
2013-12-09|2013-12-15.name: Some Strings Attached

2013-12-09|2013-12-15.description: The shocking conclusion of “Batgirl: Wanted”! Can Barbara save her father’s life without compromising the truth about her brother’s death?
2013-12-09|2013-12-15.name: Ambush

2013-12-09|2013-12-15.description:
A FOREVER EVIL tie-in! With a murderous King Shark on her tail, Amanda Waller must go deeper into the depths of Belle Reve to free a mysterious prisoner so dangerous that only she knows of his existence! Meanwhile, it’s a battle royale between the Squad’s two Gotham City psychos: Harley Quinn and James Gordon, Jr.!

For reasons still unclear, Killer Shark and his father, Kamo, are fighting to kill each other. Meanwhile, Amanda Waller tries to come up with a way to have the two powerhouses turn their rage towards the OMAC and The Thinker.

James Gordon Jr, fights Harley Quinn and tricks her into a Suicide Collar.

The Thinker gets a hold of the OMAC and attacks Kamo, giving Waller the opportunity she needs to escape.

Deadshot is still alive, and declares he is going to kill Quinn for dropping a mountain on him.

Throughout this whole issue, Waller retells the story of how she found Kamo, raised Killer Shark and the first time she witnessed the true power of OMAC.
2013-12-09|2013-12-15.name: Aloha!

2013-12-09|2013-12-15.description:
It’s Lantern vs. Lantern as John Stewart battles Hal Jordan for the leadership of the Corps! For months, John Stewart has let his anger build as Hal Jordan sent Guy Gardner into the Red Lanterns and declared war against other corps across the spectrum. After the devastating events of “LIGHTS OUT,” John is determined to rebuild the Corps as he sees fit—even if it means taking down his oldest friend!

Notes:

  • The cover is a homage to the cover of Green Lantern #3.
2013-12-09|2013-12-15.name: Homecoming

2013-12-09|2013-12-15.description: Lost in time with the Teen Titans, Superboy comes to some startling revelations about his origins and future! Can he and the team rescue Kid Flash and find the way back to their own era?
2013-12-09|2013-12-15.name: To Hell and Back

2013-12-16|2013-12-22.description: It’s double trouble as Batman investigates Harvey Dent’s past to try to find him in the present—but is he ready to face the dark truth behind Two-Face’s origin?
2013-12-16|2013-12-22.name: The Big Burn: Ignition

2013-12-16|2013-12-22.description: The last stand of Jason Todd? Ra’s al Ghul is back and more powerful than ever! The Outlaws are being held captive and Jason Todd has lost his memories…can things get any worse for the team?
2013-12-16|2013-12-22.name: Remembering

2013-12-16|2013-12-22.description:
Animal Man in outer space! How did this happen? And what will Buddy find on “THE SEED PLANET”?

Buddy Baker finds himself on a new planet surrounded by angry aliens who attack him. Animal Man is lost not being able to tap into any animal powers nearby, but when he taps into the power of the largest alien, he is able to defeat it and survive. He is then approached by Bridgewalker, who tells him he is on Seed Planet and he has been chosen to be Seed Planet's new protector.

Animal Man, refuses at first but then makes a deal, Bridgewalker will send him back to the Red and then when his family is safe he will become Seed Planet's protector for the rest of his life.

Brigewalker, after giving Animal Man new power, sends Buddy back to the Red where he becomes face to face with the King of the Limbs, who plans on killing Buddy, just like Brother Blood will kill Maxine.
